# Java Package Convention

All **new** Java classes must use `org.termx` as the root package.

- New code: `org.termx.<module>.<subpackage>`
- Existing code in `com.kodality.termx.*` is legacy; do not create new classes there.

Examples:
- `org.termx.auth` (authentication)
- `org.termx.core.sequence` (core utilities)
- `org.termx.taskforge.task` (taskforge module)

When extending or importing existing `com.kodality.*` classes from new `org.termx.*` code,
use fully qualified imports -- this is expected during the migration period.
